# Learnings

This repository contains my practice work and problem sets while studying computer science fundamentals.

---

## MIT 6.0001 – Introduction to Computer Science Using Python

### Problem Set 2 – Hangman

A console-based implementation of the Hangman game.

#### Features
- Random word selection
- Input validation
- Guess tracking
- Vowel/consonant penalty logic
- Optional hint system
- State management using functions

#### Concepts Practiced
- Control flow (loops and conditionals)
- Function design
- Boolean logic
- String manipulation
- List mutation
- Defensive programming
- Basic game state modeling

